## Section 2: Features (Demo Reel)

**Transition from Hero:** The full UI screenshot scales or morphs — the app UI panel pins to the right side of the screen (sticky) while the left side scrolls up to reveal the Features section. A vertical feature list animates in on the left. This is a sticky scroll pattern — UI on right stays fixed while feature items scroll on the left.

### Feature List Layout

Left side: vertical list of feature titles with blue dot indicators. Active feature is expanded with a short description. Inactive features are collapsed to just the title. As user scrolls (or autoplay advances), the active item changes and the video on the right updates.

**Glass effect:** If the feature video/screenshot overlaps with the UI panel, apply a subtle glassmorphism effect to handle the layering gracefully.

### Feature Item Structure
Each feature has:
- Title (short, 2-4 words)
- Description (1-2 sentences max)
- Screen recording video (`/assets/demos/feature-X.mp4`)

**Placeholder feature titles (to be updated with real copy):**
1. Map Capabilities
2. AI Q&A
3. Deep Link to Source
4. Summary View
5. Metadata View
6. Metes & Bounds
7. Aliquot Example

### Autoplay Behavior in Features
When autoplay is on, each feature video plays through, then automatically advances to the next feature. When the last feature ends, advance to the Info section. When a user clicks a feature in the list, immediately jump to that feature and pause autoplay.

